job_details.Functieomschrijving:
Our client is a global company in the food industry
     * Amersfoort
     * Detachering
     * HBO
     * 38 uur
     * Thuiswerken mogelijk

   Data & Analytics has become a key discipline for Global Procurement. We're driving competitive advantage for our client by treating procurement data and analytics as a strategic asset. Working closely with Global Category Procurement and local Business Procurement and the specialists of the global IT department, you will play a crucial role in setting up and implementing our procurement D&A strategy. You will do this together with the newly formed team of talented data, reporting and market analytics experts.

   The Data & Analytics team is engaged in many high impact projects and strategies within the procurement department. From data-driven market analysis & forecasting to smart data management, to data modelling, data science, automation and GenAI. You will have the opportunity to drive robotization projects and contribute to efficiency and automation for our client.

   The team is engaged in many high impact projects and strategies within our procurement department. From data-driven market analysis & forecasting to smart data management, to data modelling & data science. You will have the opportunity to drive the D&A agenda as a trusted business partner.

   The Procurement Data & Analytics team consists of 9 members located in the Netherlands, Hungary and Singapore. Leading procurement in data driven decision making and insights generation. Together our client is driving the Data agenda of our client, creating an engaging journey for our 300 Procurement professionals to become true data citizens.

   Tasks
     * Automating content generation (purchasing catalogues) from contracts we've closed with our suppliers;
     * Automating flow of market price data into internal Cost Price Management tool (running on PowerApps);
     * Automating various underlying parts of Source-to-Contract process;
     * Building and managing (complex) data pipelines;
     * Data staging and validation;
     * Documenting automated processes, workflows and technical specifications;
     * Collaborate with the Procurement and IT teams.

